Planet Quest is a really enjoyable game because of its music, rhythm and fun gameplay. But ever since the first few updates this game has been left as it is. I think there should be some major elements added to the game and here are a few suggestions.

1. Allow replay of the tutorial.
I like to my friends this game, but I don't want to have to delete my app and reset my high score because teaching people to play this game is difficult.

2. UFO customization
There's not much to do to this game other then the achievements, but what would be nice is playing the game to unlock cool UFO designs... They'd make good in-app purchases btw

3. New planets and animals
Planet ideas
Disco planet, Retro Planet, tutorial planet containing more song variations (I call it the marble planet)
Animal ideas
Dolphin, swims under the planet and jumps out for you to catch it.
Octopus, teleports in front of the ufo and then the planet moves backwards for you to catch it.

These are just some ideas for updates to make this game to continue to be enjoyable. And I hope that the developers come back to work on this if they want to.

I love this game, it's very interesting and the concept is nice, though there are definitely things about this game that I feel could be improved.

1. I think this game lacks structure.  A level system would be so much more fitting for a game that has quest in the title.  I get that you were going for a endless fun runner approach but I feel it just doesn't flow smoothly.

2.  Some beats just feel off.  I think (and this kinda goes with the levels comment). You should introduce characters one at a time.  Then build upon that.  A little tutorial here and there would be nice.

3.  The flowers are, to put bluntly, just dumb.  I like how most rhythm games you can play with your eyes closed and feel the beat instead of see it.  You can't do that with this game because you have to avoid flowers and I think that it looses some charm with that.  Take out the flowers, they add a tedious challenge to this game.

Overall, this is game is good, but not quite there for me to want to play this all the time, which is why I rate this game three stars.  Hopefully you see what I mean and this game can only improve from here.  I look forward to future updates, and thanks for reading!
